# Fluff Date: 2026-02-26 19:50:04
<overview>
<p>The Fredasa-class corvette is the smallest WarShip design produced by the Clans, developed during the mid-thirtieth century as a fast raider and picket vessel. Named for Ikolor Fredasa, the Commanding General of the Star League Defense Force from 2707 to 2729 and a controversial figure regarded by the Clans as the epitome of the conflicted warrior, the class emerged alongside comparable small vessels such as the Corone and Molniya during a period of modest Clan naval construction. Inner Sphere naval officers classify the Fredasa as a raider rather than a true corvette, reflecting its primary tactical role of fast strikes against vulnerable targets rather than sustained fleet engagements. The combination of high acceleration, low emergence signature, and specialized drive equipment make the design exceptionally well suited for hit-and-run operations deep behind enemy lines.</p>
</overview>

<capabilities>
<p>At just 180,000 tons, the Fredasa achieved remarkable speed for a WarShip, reaching a safe acceleration of five thrust points with a maximum of eight, enabling short bursts of four gravities. This exceptional agility was achieved through distinctive downward-thrust domes suspended below the hull, giving the vessel superlative maneuverability for its displacement class. The hull carried 131.5 tons of Valiant Lamellor ferro-carbide armor, lighter than comparable Inner Sphere corvettes but superior to Star League-era vessels of similar size. A lithium-fusion battery supplemented the compact Kearny-Fuchida drive, allowing consecutive jumps without recharging.</p><p>The weapons suite mixed capital and conventional systems for versatility. A single NAC/40 naval autocannon dominated the nose alongside two NL45 naval lasers and two Gauss rifles for forward-arc firepower. Four NAC/10 naval autocannons covered the fore quarter arcs, while additional NL45 batteries protected the broadsides and aft. Anti-fighter defense combined sixteen ER Large Lasers, sixteen ER Small Lasers, six Streak SRM-6 launchers, and four LRM-20 launchers with Artemis IV fire control systems. A single docking collar and twenty OmniFighter bays provided limited transport capacity suited to the raider mission profile.</p>
</capabilities>

<deployment>
<p>The Kerensky's Blues, originally a Clan Jade Falcon vessel, was captured at Quarell in 3055 when Blue Star Irregulars mercenaries rammed the corvette with a JumpShip to disable its command center. Wolf's Dragoons repaired the vessel, and it served the Irregulars until its destruction at Black Earth in January 3069 while shielding civilian refugees from Jade Falcon pursuit. The corvette also sustained heavy damage at Tharkad in August 3066 during engagements in the FedCom Civil War.</p><p>The CGB Black Ghost served in Clan Ghost Bear's naval reserve and was destroyed at the Second Naval Battle of Alshain in May 3067 alongside the CNC Spirit Sight, both lost during the catastrophic Trial of Retribution between the Ghost Bears and Nova Cats. The CNC Future Triumph served in Nova Cat's Transcendent Naval Star and participated in Task Force EARTHBOUND at Terra before being destroyed during the late Jihad.</p><p>The CSV Pit Viper was destroyed in October 3065 while covering the Steel Viper withdrawal from Lum during contested Trials of Possession against Clan Snow Raven. The CSR Black Beard served in the Snow Raven Circe Battle Star and was destroyed at Lum in 3070 when the Steel Viper flagship Perigard Zalman overwhelmed the Raven defensive formation in a seven-hour fleet action.</p><p>Clan Ice Hellion operated three Fredasa corvettes. The CIH Swift Bait was captured by Clan Jade Falcon during Operation ICE STORM in 3071 and rechristened Jade Tornado, remaining in Falcon service into the Dark Age. The CIH Whelp was destroyed in the Dark Nebula in March 3072 after gutting an enemy assault DropShip wave but suffering fatal armor breaches. The CIH Hellion's Pride served alongside its sister ships but its ultimate fate is undocumented.</p><p>The CDS Swift Strike survived a harrowing misjump while fleeing a Star Adder blockade at York in 3073, spending three years stranded in an unknown system and losing over half its crew before returning to Diamond Shark space in November 3077. The vessel was transferred to Clan Snow Raven around 3091, renamed Kutkh, and eventually returned to active service from mothballs during the Dark Age as part of the Alliance Naval Star.</p><p>Clan Cloud Cobra operated two examples. The CCC Perdition's Flame was destroyed in October 3075 during the Trial of Annihilation against Clan Steel Viper. The CCC Hell Fury was destroyed by Clan Goliath Scorpion during their Trial of Abjuration in 3081. One of the two had been captured from Clan Smoke Jaguar above Tanis around 3052. The CSA Arcadian Asp and CSA Vicious Fang participated in Star Adder Watch operations during the Wars of Reaving, including orbital bombardment of Dark Caste positions at Ghent, and remained among Star Adder's thirteen operational WarShips by 3085.</p>
</deployment>

<history>
<p>The Fredasa entered service around 2962, during a period when several Clans were constructing small WarShip designs to supplement their aging Star League-era fleets. Approximately sixteen keels were laid down across multiple Clans, with the design seeing widespread adoption among both Warden and Crusader factions. The class competed for yard time with the Corone and Molniya corvettes but proved the most enduring of the three. By the time of Operation Revival in 3049, the Fredasa was the only small Clan-designed WarShip class still in active service, with examples serving in the naval forces of Clans Ghost Bear, Nova Cat, Steel Viper, Ice Hellion, Star Adder, Cloud Cobra, Diamond Shark, Snow Raven, Jade Falcon, and Smoke Jaguar.</p><p>The sheer number of Clans operating the design meant that Fredasa corvettes appeared across a wide range of operational theaters during the Invasion era. Clan Smoke Jaguar maintained at least two hulls that were scuttled above Huntress in 3060 rather than allow their capture during the Inner Sphere counterattack. A Jade Falcon vessel was seized by mercenary forces at Quarell in 3055 through unorthodox boarding tactics, marking the first Clan WarShip to fall into Inner Sphere hands. The incident demonstrated that even the smallest Clan naval assets were not invulnerable to determined opposition willing to discard conventional engagement protocols.</p><p>The Wars of Reaving proved devastating for the class, claiming vessels across nearly every conflict of the period. Two corvettes were lost at the Second Naval Battle of Alshain in May 3067 during a Trial of Retribution between Clans Ghost Bear and Nova Cat. A Steel Viper vessel was destroyed covering a withdrawal at Lum in October 3065, and a Snow Raven corvette fell at the same world during a brutal engagement against the Steel Viper flagship Perigard Zalman in 3070. Clan Ice Hellion lost two of its three hulls during Operation ICE STORM, with one destroyed in combat and another captured by Clan Jade Falcon. Cloud Cobra operations during the Reaving cost them one vessel in combat against the Steel Vipers and another to Clan Goliath Scorpion during the latter Clan's Trial of Abjuration in 3081. A Diamond Shark corvette endured a misjump and three years stranded in an unknown system before limping back to civilization. The cumulative losses reduced the class from widespread service to a scattered handful of survivors.</p><p>By the ilClan era, Clan transfers and wartime captures had redistributed the remaining Fredasa corvettes among a few successor factions. The Raven Alliance brought a long-mothballed hull back into active service during the Dark Age, while Star Adder retained two operational examples in the Homeworlds. The class record stretched across nearly two centuries of continuous Clan service, an exceptional lifespan for a design of such modest displacement.</p>
</history>

